The Revanites are a splinter faction of Malak’s Sith Empire. After Revan’s fall, they are those who took issue with Malak’s new, more destructive war, and threw in with Lord Valerius, supporting his rebellion against the Darth and bid to claim the title of Dark Lord of the Sith. For some their loyalty is to Valerius, others to their idea of who Revan was and what he stood for, others simply take issue with Darth Malak, and some still seek out the Revanites for their less despicable tendencies as far as Sith go, seeing them more as the Jedi Crusaders of the late Mandalorian Wars than the monsters that compose the Sith Empire. Regardless, they are still followers of the Dark Side.

The Revanites promote competition amongst their ranks, both among the Force Sensitives among their number and their rank and file troops. Those the most merciless, cruel and powerful amongst them are elevated, while those exhibiting softer tendencies are treated like fodder and find death sooner rather than later - often from friendly fire.

These are the former among them. Clad in finer armor and given access to the newest in Imperial weapons technology as reward for their faithful service to the Sith.

Sith Sorcerers are among the most vile of individuals. Using ancient techniques they defile the very nature of reality, twisting the Force itself to serve their ambitions. The strongest among them are known to have a draining effect on those around them, sapping the light itself from the hearts of those who would otherwise oppose them.

Acolyte Lunari is known for her fierce intellect and an intense devotion to the Revanite Order. One of the rising stars of the Order, amongst her many tasks include the assessment of fresh prospects seeking to become Aspirants.

Sith warriors are legendary combatants, using the Dark Side of the Force to enhance their physical attributes well beyond what is considered natural. At the same time, it has corrupted them to their very core. As time goes on, they become less human and more and embodiment of the same primal emotions that grant them their strength.

The strongest among them are known to have a draining effect on those around them, sapping the light itself from the hearts of those who would otherwise oppose them.

Lord Arrelac is one of those elevated with the founding of the Twilight Praxeum. Appointed to oversee the Sith chambers, he spends much of his time training new aspirants, and imparting the Revanite philosophies upon those new to the Order. He is a man of stern but practical disposition, and has been attributed a generosity rare amongst his peers. Nevertheless, his rare displays of wrath and displeasure have been sufficient to violently convince those who may disrespect him the unhealthy errors of their ways.

Carved upon this plaque is writ thus:

WARNING: THE ASPIRANT'S TRIAL.

ASPIRANTS ONLY. ONE AT A TIME.

NO INTERFERENCE.

ON PENALTY OF FAILURE, EXILE, OR EXECUTION.
